  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "For example, I want to run my `geth` with some sort of `config-file.yaml`\n\n```\nallowedMethods\n  - eth_GetBalance\n```\n\nMy options for having this feature (so far, as I just read the code for 1 hour), in order from most to less hacky:\n- Fork `geth` everytime it has a new release, and mess up with the service registration.\n- Put some node.js / golang proxy, read the request body and perform the restriction.\n- Ask you guys if you would be interested in this feature and auto-assign it.\n\nPlease people, do point me to the right way to discuss this feature. I consider it not trivial (nor frivolous), as it impacts my job as sysadmin of geth nodes.\n\nCC: @kumavis @flyswatter @Firescar96\n",
